The Senator representing Niger South Senatorial District, Muhammed Bima Enagi, has promised to embark on programmes that will reduce unemployment and poverty among youths and women in the state. Senator Enagi made the promise in Abuja during a reception organised in his honour to mark his inauguration as a member of the 9th Senate. According to the lawmaker who was elected on the platform of APC, youths and women formed the major population of the country hence the need to empower them. He also promised to carry out programmes that would promote the development of education in the state. Niger: Reducing unemployment is my priority - Senator Enagi Sheikh Saeedu Muhammad Enagi (1952-2011) ADC guber candidate congratulates Gov Bello, calls for inclusive govt Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin